<part id="intro">
  <title>Introduction</title>

  <para>
    CtkSourceView is a <ulink url="https://www.gnome.org/">GNOME</ulink> library
    that extends CtkTextView, the standard CTK+ widget for multiline text
    editing. CtkSourceView adds support for syntax highlighting, undo/redo, file
    loading and saving, search and replace, a completion system, printing,
    displaying line numbers, and other features typical of a source code editor.
  </para>

  <para>
    See the <ulink url="https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/CtkSourceView">CtkSourceView website</ulink>.
  </para>

  <para>
    CtkSourceView @GSV_API_VERSION@ depends on CTK+ 3.
  </para>

  <refsect1>
    <title>pkg-config name</title>
    <para>
      For CtkSourceView @GSV_API_VERSION@, the pkg-config name is:
      <code>ctksourceview-@GSV_API_VERSION@</code>
    </para>
    <para>
      To compile a program that uses CtkSourceView @GSV_API_VERSION@, you
      can for example use the following command:
    </para>
    <para>
      <code>$ gcc hello.c `pkg-config --cflags --libs ctksourceview-@GSV_API_VERSION@` -o hello</code>
    </para>
  </refsect1>
</part>
